Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{0.25%tsp} on high heat. Add
the @Jasmine Rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and
leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, trim the @Green Beans{80%grams}, then cut into thirds. Drain the
@King Prawns{225%grams}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the prawns and green beans. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir-fry until the prawns are cooked through, ~{4-5%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns. Cook so they're
> opaque in the middle.

While the prawns and beans are frying, in a #small bowl{}, combine the
@Ginger, Garlic & Lemongrass Puree{22%grams}, @Ketjap Manis{50%grams} and
@Sambal Paste{15%grams}.

> Add less sambal if you'd prefer things milder.

Mix in the @Honey{1%tbsp} and @Water for the Sauce{75%milliliter(s)}, then set aside.

Once cooked, add the @Coleslaw Mix{120%grams} to the prawn pan and sprinkle over
the @Indonesian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}.

Stir-fry until fragrant and the veg has slightly softened, ~{1%min}.

Add an extra drizzle of oil if needed.

When the prawns are cooked and the veg is tender, stir the sauce mixture into the
pan and cook until thickened slightly, ~{1-2%mins}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if you
feel it needs it.

Fluff up the rice and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the prawn and veg stir-fry.

Spoon over any remaining sauce from the pan to finish. Enjoy!